  "text": "The CSS style rendering pipeline in Chromium's Blink engine is implemented across multiple key components:\n\n1. **StyleResolver** (`third_party/blink/renderer/core/css/resolver/style_resolver.h`, line 63): This is the primary class that resolves computed styles for DOM elements. The `StyleResolver::ResolveStyle()` method takes an Element and a StyleRecalcContext and returns a ComputedStyle. There is a 1-1 relationship between StyleResolver and Document, with the resolver maintaining the collection of stylesheets (user, author, and UA styles) for style computation. The header file indicates it's a garbage-collected class that handles stylesheet cascade resolution and computed style creation.\n\n2. **LayoutObject** (`third_party/blink/renderer/core/layout/layout_object.h`, line 270): This is the base class for all layout tree objects in Blink. LayoutObjects form a tree structure closely mapping the DOM tree, with the LayoutView as the root. The class manages the layout tree structure, layout computation, sizing/positioning of DOM nodes, and provides the foundation for rendering calculations. It inherits from GarbageCollected, ImageResourceObserver, and DisplayItemClient, making it central to the rendering pipeline.\n\n3. **PaintLayer** (`third_party/blink/renderer/core/paint/paint_layer.h`, line 174): This class handles the painting layer abstraction and is central to the painting and hit-testing systems. PaintLayer manages complex painting operations including opacity, clipping, filters, reflections, and hardware acceleration. It handles the concept of \"self-painting layers\" which determines how LayoutObjects are painted. PaintLayer also manages the stacking context and coordinates with PaintLayerCompositor for composited layers.\n\n4. **DisplayItemList** (`third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/paint/display_item_list.h`, line 28): This is a container class for a list of display items of various types. It's defined in the graphics/paint subsystem and serves as the fundamental data structure for recording paint operations. The DisplayItemList stores display items that have been generated during the paint walk, which are later converted into paint chunks and rendering commands.\n\n5. **PaintController** (`third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/paint/paint_controller.h`, line 131): This is the core class responsible for processing display items and producing a final paint artifact. It includes logic for caching, cache invalidation, and merging paint operations. PaintController works with DisplayItemList to manage the recording of paint operations and is defined in the platform graphics subsystem. It processes paint chunks and recording information to generate optimized rendering output.\n\nThe rendering pipeline flows as: CSS styles are resolved by StyleResolver → computed styles are applied to LayoutObjects in the layout tree → PaintLayer organizes the layout tree for painting → display items are recorded to DisplayItemList → PaintController processes and caches these items to produce the final paint artifact for rendering."
}

